What are some good guidelines in selecting a the secret keys for
a Diffie-Hellman exchange ?

Secure RPC uses 192 bit modulus....in Applied Cryptography Schneier suggests:
"n should be large: at least 512 bits long. Using 1028 bits would be better"
[a really good book, BTW]

...so exactly how in secure IS Secure RPC ? :)


